(43, 2, 19, 41, 15, 29, 29, NULL, 'Connection of Temple Destruction', 'Both passages emphasize the destruction of the temple and its restoration in three days. This connection highlights the significance of Jesus'' statement about the temple in the context of his crucifixion and the mockery he faced.', 'quotation', 0.43299999999999994, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 2, 19, 40, 27, 40, 40, 'Destroy this temple, and in three days', 'Connection of Temple Destruction', 'Both passages emphasize the destruction of the temple and its rebuilding in three days. This connection highlights the challenge to Jesus'' authority and identity as the Son of God.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 2, 19, 40, 26, 60, 61, 'Destroy this temple, and in three days I will raise it up', 'Connection of Temple Destruction', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of destroying the temple and raising it in three days. This connection highlights the significance of Jesus'' statement regarding the temple in both contexts.', 'quotation', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 2, 19, 45, 8, 11, 11, 'in three days I will raise it up', 'Resurrection and Spiritual Life', 'This connection highlights the theme of resurrection in both passages. John 2:19 speaks of Jesus raising the temple in three days, while Romans 8:11 emphasizes the Spirit that raised Jesus also quickens believers'' bodies.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 2, 19, 43, 10, 17, 18, 'I will raise it up', 'Resurrection and Authority Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of resurrection and the authority of Jesus over his life and death. In John 2:19, Jesus speaks of raising the temple in three days, while in John 10:17-18, he asserts his power to lay down and take up his life.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 2, 19, 44, 2, 32, 32, 'in three days I will raise it up', 'Resurrection of Jesus', 'This connection highlights the theme of Jesus'' resurrection. In John 2:19, Jesus speaks of raising the temple in three days, which is fulfilled in Acts 2:32 where God raises Jesus.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 2, 21, 46, 6, 19, 19, 'temple of his body', 'Body as Temple Connection', 'This connection highlights the concept of the body as a temple. John 2:21 refers to Jesus'' body as the temple, while 1 Corinthians 6:19 emphasizes that believers'' bodies are temples of the Holy Ghost.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 2, 21, 46, 3, 16, 16, 'temple of his body', 'Connection of Divine Presence', 'This connection highlights the concept of the body as a temple. Both passages emphasize the significance of the temple, with John referring to Jesus'' body and Paul to believers as the temple of God.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 2, 21, 49, 2, 20, 22, 'temple of his body', 'Connection of the Temple Concept', 'This connection highlights the theme of the temple as a representation of God''s presence. John 2:21 refers to Jesus'' body as the temple, while Ephesians 2:20-22 speaks of believers being built together as a holy temple in the Lord.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 2, 21, 51, 1, 19, 19, 'temple of his body', 'Connection of Christ and Fulness', 'This connection highlights the embodiment of divine presence in Christ. John 2:21 refers to the ''temple of his body,'' while Colossians 1:19 speaks of the ''fulness'' dwelling in him, emphasizing the significance of Christ as the ultimate manifestation of God''s presence.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 2, 21, 51, 2, 9, 9, 'temple of his body', 'Connection of Body and Godhead', 'This connection highlights the significance of the body in both passages. John 2:21 refers to the temple of Jesus'' body, while Colossians 2:9 emphasizes the fullness of the Godhead dwelling in Him bodily.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
